Jira is a tool used by software teams to track work, bugs, and tasks.
Think of it like a digital to-do list for a whole team.

Example:

Developer finds a bug → creates a ticket in Jira

Team member works on it → updates the status

Manager tracks progress → through boards and reports
------------------------------------------------------------->
Very Simple Example (Imagine Your Work Day)
-------------------------------------------------------------->
Suppose your manager says:

“Fix login issue in the app”

In Jira it will look like a ticket.

Ticket Example

Title: Fix login API failure
Description: Users cannot login when password contains special characters
Assignee: You
Status: To Do → In Progress → Done

You open the ticket → work → update status.






