Main Things in Jira (Only 5 You Must Know)
1️⃣ Issue / Ticket

This is a task.

Examples:

Fix bug

Build feature

Write API

Investigate error

Types:

Bug

Task

Story

Epic (big feature)
2️⃣ Board

A board shows all tasks visually.

Columns usually:

To Do
In Progress
In Review
Done

You simply drag the task to next column when progress changes.

Example:

Login Bug
To Do → In Progress → Done

3️⃣ Sprint

If team follows Agile / Scrum, work happens in 2 weeks cycles.

Example Sprint:

Sprint 1
Duration: 2 weeks

Tasks:
Fix login bug
Create payment API
Improve UI

You pick tasks from Backlog → Sprint

4️⃣ Backlog

Backlog = list of all future tasks

Think of it like:

Future work list

Manager or product owner decides what goes into sprint.

5️⃣ Workflow (Status changes)

Example workflow:

To Do
 ↓
In Progress
 ↓
Code Review
 ↓
Testing
 ↓
Done

You only change the status while working.

What YOU Will Actually Do Daily (Reality)

When working in a company:

Morning

Open Jira

See tickets assigned to you

Start working

Change status → In Progress

While working

Add comments like:

Investigating the issue.
Root cause found in auth service.
Fix in progress.
After finishing
Push code
Create pull request
Move ticket → Code Review
After approval

Move to:

Done
Basic Things You Must Learn (Very Easy)

Create ticket

Assign ticket

Change status

Add comment

Attach screenshot / logs

That's 90% of Jira usage.

Example Ticket
Title: Fix payment failure

Description:
Users getting 500 error while making payment.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Login
2. Add product
3. Click pay

Expected:
Payment success

Actual:
500 error

Priority: High
Assignee: Srivas
One Real Tip (Important for Your Career)

Many developers lose reputation because they don't update Jira.

Always update:

Started working
Issue found
Fix done
Waiting for review

Managers track progress through Jira.




